1-You could use the ppa for the almost-always latest version:

   . sudo add-apt-repository ppa:cwchien/gradle
   . sudo apt-get update
   . sudo apt upgrade gradle
  
2 - or SDKMAN for the latest version:

   . curl -s "https://get.sdkman.io" | bash
   . source "$HOME/.sdkman/bin/sdkman-init.sh"
   . sdk install gradle
   
   
   nb:Advantages of the ppa
   
   auto-updates with the system
   no piping of downloaded scripts to the shell
   
   Advantages of sdkman: latest version supplied by gradle themselves.
   
   
   
   
   lien du tutoriel :https://askubuntu.com/questions/932083/how-do-i-upgrade-gradle
